Heathrow Airport arrest: Teen in custody on suspicion of terrorism
The 19-year-old is currently in custody and being questioned by counter-terrorism police at a station in south London. Officers have searched an address near Camden, north London, in relation to the arrest. Metropolitan Police said in a statement: "The arrest is not in response to any immediate risk or threat."
Police later confirmed the incident was "Syria-related".
The investigation is still ongoing.